To: Wild Bill<br><br>
I understand your point of view and sensitivity to respect for human life. <br><br>
I too am beginning to respect my own life, neglected for over 26 years. My dilemma stems from conflicting feelings about human life spawned from my Vietnam experience. My feelings that are beginning to emerge are polarized. On one hand, disregard for human life was the essence of survival. On the other hand, the preservation of human life was a violated sanctity. I have relentless reminders of both.<br><br>
It really makes me very sad. I do cry about it from time to time.<br><br>
You alluded to a search for truth. I find myself looking for truth in the events and feelings that constantly circle in my mind. I agree that the truth is not necessarily what we were told. I also know that the truth was not necessarily what we saw, either. For me, the truth still lies elusively somewhere in the middle.<br><br>
I hope time and perserverance will get me closer.<br><br>
 
